observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Management agreed to:
Require the MASSO to create a task force to prioritize working on the titling of all the LGU-owned lots. Funds be sufficiently appropriated and made available to defray expenses relative to titling;
Require the Municipal Accountant to retrieve or secure the documentary requirements as required in COA Circular 2012-001 pertaining to all lot acquisitions and submit the same to this Office;
Require the Municipal Accountant to maintain RPLC as prescribed in the NGAS for LGU Volume 2 and record the acquisition, description, addition/improvements, disposal, and other information for each class of real property (land). Transactions affecting each real property such as cost of survey, etc. shall be posted from source documents promptly therein;
Require the Municipal Accountant to update the Land account as per Subsidiary Ledger in consonance with the record of the MASSO.

We recommend that Management:
1.	Ensure that documents are prepared and dated at the appropriate time to prevent having conflicting entries making the whole procurement process unreliable;
2.	Instruct the BAC to carefully review the accreditation and eligibility of prospective bidders and award items only if they are actually carried in stock by them;
3.	Instruct those preparing the Accomplishment Reports to properly accomplish and review the entries so as to reflect the actual and accurate percentage of work done.

